&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Accounting Clerk&lt;/strong&gt; experienced in managing our liquidity and vendor ecosystem with precision, ensuring seamless global settlements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain supplier and customer reports, monitor AR and AP balances, and provide real-time financial information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review expense claims and reimbursements for compliance, appropriateness of categories and amounts, and validity of supporting documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage end-to-end accounts receivable process, including contract review, customer reconciliation, invoicing, and cash application to ensure accuracy, timeliness, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee supplier file management, AP reconciliation, payment terms, invoice verification, and processing of payment requests in line with contracts and company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with suppliers and customers on invoices and reconciliations, resolve outstanding issues, and support business operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform regular AP aging analysis, identify abnormal items, and ensure completeness of liability records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File and archive supplier, customer, and daily reimbursement documents properly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in inventory counts and audit support to maintain compliant and accurate financial records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle end-to-end export customs declarations: collect order information, apply and write off numbers on third-party platforms, submit via Customs Single Window, provide documentation to brokers/forwarders, track progress, and resolve corrections for smooth cargo clearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and reconcile complete customs documents for three-way matching and closed-loop management; maintain systematic filing with consistent time sequencing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow rotation schedules, complete daily handovers and Customs Declaration Handover Log, and remain available outside working hours for urgent matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm cargo and loading details with business teams, submit timely VAT Refund filings, liaise with customs/brokers/platforms to resolve issues, and support foreign exchange settlement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the Export Customs Declaration Ledger, submit weekly reports to the Finance Manager, monitor policy changes, propose improvements, resolve inspections/mismatches/disputes, and build strong relationships with customs authorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete other relevant tasks assigned by management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree or Diploma Holder in Accounting, Business or related disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ year of hands-on experience in various accounting functions, including general bookkeeping and managing Accounts Receivable and Payable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with written communication in both English and Cantonese.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good computer knowledge, including Microsoft Office, Google Workspace and Chinese Word Processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated sense of responsibility, self-motivation, and a proactive attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong team player with meticulous attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, manage multiple tasks simultaneously, and consistently meet tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CASETiFY is one of the leading global lifestyle brands to offer customizable tech accessories. We’re industry leaders when it comes to trend forecasting and protecting what matters most; the community platform for creativity and self-expression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an international company that cares about culture and diversity. Our group is headquartered in Hong Kong and has offices in Los Angeles, Seoul, Shanghai, Taipei, Tokyo and our team comes from 30+ nationalities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We stand up for what we believe in by supporting causes that matter to us and our global community. At CASETiFY, we embrace diversity and inclusivity. As an equal opportunity employer, we encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply. We are also committed to sponsoring work visas on behalf of qualified candidates if necessary.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY seeks a highly motivated and driven individual for the &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Business Development Manager&lt;/strong&gt; position within our &lt;strong&gt;Global Wholesale team&lt;/strong&gt;. Reporting directly to the Senior Manager of Global Wholesale Team, this role will be pivotal in expanding our global presence and establishing strategic partnerships. The ideal candidate will possess strong leadership, communication, and analytical skills, coupled with a passion for driving business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly manage and grow the full portfolio of &lt;strong&gt;APAC distributor accounts&lt;/strong&gt; (including ANZ), ensuring operational excellence and maximizing account revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spearhead the development of new business partnerships and wholesale distribution channels, with a primary focus on the ANZ market and strategic B2B co-lab opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage complex, collaborative &lt;strong&gt;B2B wholesale co-lab projects&lt;/strong&gt; and marketing initiatives, ensuring alignment with global strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage project timelines, deliverables, and budgets,&lt;/strong&gt; and operational expenditures for all B2B co-lab and distribution initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with internal and external stakeholders to guarantee successful project implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth market research, develop detailed sales forecasts, and provide &lt;strong&gt;data-driven insights&lt;/strong&gt; to inform APAC distribution and B2B strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and guide junior team members to cultivate a positive work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or higher in Business Management, Marketing, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience is mandatory in the global wholesale distribution or consumer products sector.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional problem-solving and interpersonal skills, with a proven ability to remain calm and effective under pressure and demonstrate strong adaptability in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong understanding of global wholesale market dynamics, business development principles, and proficient data processing/analysis skills to support strategic account management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven capacity for working independently with high standards of reliability and ownership over a portfolio of key regional accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English, with excellent verbal and written communication and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CASETiFY&lt;/strong&gt; is recruiting &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Contract Manager&lt;/strong&gt;/ &lt;strong&gt;Paralegal &lt;/strong&gt;to join our Legal team. Reporting to both the Legal Director and the Contract Manager, this role will support the contract team in the preparation, drafting, and review of commercial contracts and other legal documents. Additionally, this role will support compliance matters, focusing on researching regulations and maintaining internal regulatory compliance policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As the ideal candidate, you will have solid experience in working with internal clients to review contracts and legal documents, as well as regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing, drafting, and reviewing commercial contracts and other legal documents, including license agreements, marketing agreements, artist and influencer agreements, service agreements with third-party vendors, and confidentiality agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with internal clients on contracts and legal documents review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide translation on contracts/agreements where necessary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing and implementing internal regulatory compliance policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing and maintaining a regulatory library, including research, and keep up-to-date on the regulatory development in the areas mentioned above and other areas as necessary (such as employment law)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as may be assigned from time to time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in handling contract review and regulatory compliance concerning data privacy, consumer protection, marketing, and advertising in an in-house environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree/Diploma in Legal Studies - Holder of a Bachelor’s Degree in other disciplines with solid experience in contracting review and drafting will also be considered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-organized, analytical-minded, and detail-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working independently with the ability to plan, organize and prioritize task&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong legal research, problem-solving, and decision-making skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word &amp;amp; Excel)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English and Traditional &amp;amp; Simplified Chinese&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Immediate availability is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates with more experience will be considered as Assistant Contract Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Finance Manager&lt;/strong&gt; in our Shenzhen Finance hub. You will be managing full-set accounts and intricate production costs for our HQ and logistic hubs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage end-to-end general ledger accounting, prepare journal vouchers and financial statements to ensure accurate, authentic, and compliant books.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle document workflows across business and financial systems; reconcile order data monthly, perform cost accounting, and period-end closing to deliver timely and accurate reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly management reports, verify cost and inventory data, analyze variances, identify issues, and propose actionable improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support budget management, financial analysis, and forecasting; liaise with branch offices, ensure regulatory compliance, and maintain strong cross-functional communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide business and operational insights to management; identify issues, recommend solutions, and deliver decision support to achieve strategic targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in annual budget formulation, monitor execution, flag deviations, and recommend corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee daily financial receipts and payments, control costs and expenses, analyze departmental spending, and implement measures to improve profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in optimizing cost and inventory processes, including regular counts to ensure book-physical consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support accounting process improvements, financial digitalization, and the establishment of a standardized framework while continuously refining policies and workflows to ensure full compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate external audits, government filings, high-tech enterprise qualification, and subsidy applications; prepare materials and follow through to completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with business departments to explain financial data, provide timely support and handle ad-hoc assignments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree or Diploma Holder in Accounting, Business, or related disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of related working experience. Experience within the E-commerce or Retail sectors is a definite advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in accounting software is required; familiarity with NetSuite is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills in both English and Cantonese.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated sense of responsibility, self-motivation, and a proactive attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong team player with meticulous attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, manage multiple tasks simultaneously, and consistently meet tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CASETiFY is one of the leading global lifestyle brands to offer customizable tech accessories. We’re industry leaders when it comes to trend forecasting and protecting what matters most; the community platform for creativity and self-expression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an international company that cares about culture and diversity. Our group is headquartered in Hong Kong and has offices in Los Angeles, Seoul, Shanghai, Taipei, Tokyo and our team comes from 27+ nationalities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We stand up for what we believe in by supporting causes that matter to us and our global community. At CASETiFY, we embrace diversity and inclusivity. As an equal opportunity employer, we encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply. We are also committed to sponsoring work visas on behalf of qualified candidates if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY is seeking an entrepreneurial, creative, and passionate &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Growth Marketing Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join our Growth team. As the ideal candidate, you will hit the ground running, thrive in a fast-paced environment, and be detail-oriented. You are a self-starter and team player who can quickly identify opportunities to create procedures that increase efficiencies, scalability, and effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will lead our Google performance engine. You are responsible for developing and implementing a comprehensive Google marketing strategy that aligns with our global business goals. You will drive the execution of advanced bidding strategies (including Performance Max), search intent optimization, and visual storytelling across YouTube to maximize ROAS and long-term ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Strategy &amp;amp; Execution: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop and execute an end-to-end Google performance strategy across Search, Performance Max (PMAX), Display, and YouTube to drive new customer acquisition and brand equity on a global scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Oversee the day-to-day operations of large-scale, multi-country Google Ads accounts, including campaign structure, budget pacing, and bid management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimization &amp;amp; Testing: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead a rigorous, continuous A/B testing roadmap for ad copy, landing pages, and audience signals to identify growth levers and improve conversion rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Driven Insights: &lt;/strong&gt;Analyze complex user data and GA4 insights to provide actionable feedback on marketing efficiency. Monitor country-specific performance to identify regional growth opportunities or inefficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative Collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner closely with the Creative and Content teams to produce high-performing visual assets for YouTube and the Google Display Network, ensuring all content meets both brand aesthetic standards and performance KPIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Scaling:&lt;/strong&gt; Stay ahead of industry trends and Google’s product roadmap (including Alpha/Beta features) to maintain a competitive edge and scale CASETiFY’s global presence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree or above in Business, Marketing, or a related discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in digital marketing with a minimum of 3 years of hands-on experience in Google Ads, managing significant budgets for premium consumer brands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in Google Merchant Center, Search Ads 360, and GA4. Experience with Performance Max (PMax) is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of Microsoft Office and Goo

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CASETiFY&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking a data-driven &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Marketing Manager&lt;/strong&gt; for Performance Marketing to drive local growth and optimize our digital acquisition funnel. In this role, you will scale our performance marketing channels, manage key paid and organic platforms in Korea, and design seamless CRM customer journeys. You will balance strategic planning with hands-on execution to maximize return on ad spend (ROAS) and customer lifetime value (LTV).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Marketing &amp;amp; Local Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute Paid Media: Plan, launch, and optimize Naver Brand Search, SEM, Display Ads (DA), and blog marketing campaigns to drive local user growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Paid Messaging: Oversee KakaoTalk DM (Direct Messaging) strategies and target segmentations to boost conversions and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize Funnels: Conduct continuous A/B testing on ad creatives, landing pages, and audience targeting to improve conversion rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Control Budget: Manage the performance marketing budget, track expenses, and ensure optimal ROAS across all digital channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CRM &amp;amp; Content Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build CRM Journeys: Work closely with the Global CRM team to design, implement, and automate full-lifecycle CRM journeys to increase local user engagement and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Local Email Marketing Calendar: Develop and execute high-performing EDM (Electronic Direct Mail) campaigns, analyzing open and click-through rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on Creatives: Work with internal teams to develop engaging localized content for websites, newsletters, and social media.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Intelligence &amp;amp; Activation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze Data: Monitor campaign metrics daily using analytics tools to provide actionable insights and performance reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct Research: Track local market trends, user preferences, and competitor performance marketing tactics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Vendors: Maintain strong relationships with external agencies, ad networks, and localized platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education: &lt;/strong&gt;University degree in Business Administration, Marketing, or a related discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum of 6 years of hands-on experience in performance marketing, growth marketing, or digital media buying.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills: &lt;/strong&gt;Proficiency with marketing analytics tools and CRM automation software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Channel Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Deep understanding of the Korean digital ecosystem, specifically Naver (SEM/DA/Blog) and KakaoTalk ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Skills: &lt;/strong&gt;Sharp project management skills, exceptional attention to detail, and a highly analytical mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Languages: &lt;/strong&gt;Native Korean with a professional working proficiency level of English (mandatory).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Soft Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong communication and presentation skills are highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Location: 凤岗镇雁田村&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY is one of the leading global lifestyle brands to offer customizable tech accessories. We&#39;re &lt;strong&gt;industry&lt;/strong&gt; leaders when it comes to trend forecasting and protecting what matters most; the community platform for creativity and self-expression. We are expanding our team in order to deliver the best-in-market engagement and products for our growing community.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inventory &amp;amp; Process Management
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inventory Control: Oversee end-to-end inventory management to ensure accuracy and optimal stock levels across multiple nodes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systems Management: Operate and monitor ERP and WMS systems to ensure data integrity between physical stock and digital records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Optimisation: Continuously evaluate and refine logistics workflows to reduce lead times and operational costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customs Compliance: Knowledge with export customs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner &amp;amp; Vendor Management
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3PL Coaching: Onboard, train, and coach third-party logistics (3PL) providers specifically on Casetify’s unique logistics processes and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resource Sourcing: Leverage existing networks and identify new E-commerce service providers to scale our global footprint.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supplier Training: Assign tasks and provide structured training to third-party suppliers to ensure KPIs and Service Level Agreements (SLAs) are consistently met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data &amp;amp; Analysis
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Management: Utilize advanced Excel skills and system-generated reports to analyze logistics data, identifying bottlenecks and forecasting future resource needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting: Create clear, actionable reports on logistics performance and cost-efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor degree with major in logistics, supply chain management, International Trade/Business, Industrial Engineering is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: Proven experience in logistics management, preferably within the E-commerce or consumer electronics sector. 5+ years working experience in supply chain or logistics is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Skills:&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of ERP and WMS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excel Expert: Expert-level Excel skills (VLOOKUP, Pivot Tables, etc.) and strong data management capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance: Deep understanding of logistics processes and customs declaration procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication:&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native or professional fluency in English and Mandarin (written and verbal) is essential for coordinating with global teams and regional suppliers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soft Skills:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem-Solving: Exceptional ability to troubleshoot issues under pressure and &quot;act fast&quot; to mitigate delays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attitude: A highly collaborative &quot;can-do&quot; working attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpersonal: Strong communication skills to effectively coach and influence external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working Location
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great Bay Area / Multiple working locations and willing to travel within the Great Bay Area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CASETiFY is one of the leading global lifestyle brands to offer customizable tech accessories. We’re industry leaders when it comes to trend forecasting and protecting what matters most; the community platform for creativity and self-expression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an international company that cares about culture and diversity. Our group is headquartered in Hong Kong and has offices in Los Angeles, Seoul, Shanghai, Taipei, Tokyo and our team comes from 27+ nationalities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We stand up for what we believe in by supporting causes that matter to us and our global community. At CASETiFY, we embrace diversity and inclusivity. As an equal opportunity employer, we encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply. We are also committed to sponsoring work visas on behalf of qualified candidates if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY is now seeking an entrepreneurial, creative, and passionate &lt;strong&gt;Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Partnerships&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Manager&lt;/strong&gt; who will directly report to the Partnerships Manager to join our Global Partnership team. As the ideal candidate, you will hit the ground running, thrive in a fast-paced environment, and be detail-oriented. You must be a self-starter and a team player who can quickly identify areas of opportunity to create procedures that increase efficiencies, scalability, and effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will support the rapid expansion of the Global market by researching, connecting with, and updating trends in global brand opportunities. You will execute collaboration collections and marketing campaigns to drive business growth according to the company&#39;s direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute collaboration projects to drive business growth according to the company&#39;s direction. Plan and deploy marketing and collaboration launch campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive project management and stakeholder relations across internal teams and external partners; align creative feedback, marketing assets and launch timelines to ensure seamless, on-time product delivery&lt;/li&gt;
