&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CASETiFY is seeking a sophisticated tax professional to oversee our global fiscal footprint. The &lt;strong&gt;Global Taxation Manager&lt;/strong&gt; will be responsible for ensuring regulatory compliance while providing strategic insights into our international expansion. This role demands a high level of technical precision, a data-driven mindset, and the ability to navigate complex cross-border tax environments within a fast-paced, high-growth corporate structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and execute the end-to-end indirect tax compliance (VAT/GST/Sales Tax) across all operating markets, ensuring full accuracy and timely filing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain the Group’s Transfer Pricing documentation. Monitor intercompany transactions to ensure they adhere to arm&#39;s length principles and support the global supply chain strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the supply chain teams to evaluate the tax implications of international trade routes and identify opportunities for fiscal efficiency and duty optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the tax consultant for new market entries. This includes managing tax registrations, identifying local tax risks, and establishing the structural foundation for new legal entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor global tax legislative changes and assess their potential impact on the business. Provide clear, actionable briefings to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Legal and Finance to establish and monitor intercompany transactions, management fees, and cost-sharing arrangements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead periodic internal tax reviews and coordinate with external auditors to ensure robust control environments and minimize exposure during tax inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with logistics teams to leverage Free Trade Agreements (FTAs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting, Finance, or Law. Professional accreditation (CPA, CTA, or equivalent) is mandatory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional experience in taxation, with significant exposure to indirect tax and transfer pricing. A background in a Big 4 firm or a multinational corporation (MNC) is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to interpret complex data sets and translate them into strategic financial recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with global indirect tax regimes and customs regulations is an asset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of Microsoft Office and Google Workspace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of English (written and verbal). Ability to communicate complex tax concepts to non-finance stakeholders with clarity and poise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with the ability to manage multiple high-priority projects simultaneously under rigorous deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in fast-paced, &quot;startup-to-scaleup&quot; environments and are passionate about design, tech accessories, and the lifestyle industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A candidate with less experience will be considered for the &lt;strong&gt;Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Taxation&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Manager position&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

