&lt;li&gt;This is not a pure execution role; it requires a relentless growth mindset that drills down into the &quot;why&quot; behind performance data and immediately creates the &quot;how&quot; to execute the next iteration. You will use advanced data platforms to understand exactly why an ad wins or loses, applying those insights to lead cross-functional teams in producing high-converting, trust-building content tailored specifically for the US consumer that directly impacts the bottom line. At the core of this content is compelling storytelling; you will act as the voice of the brand, translating our values into authentic narratives that build deep trust and long-term relationships with our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;A) Creative Intelligence &amp;amp; Analytics (Core Focus)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Find the Winning Formula:&lt;/strong&gt; Utilize hands-on creative analysis experience to drill into performance data. Track metrics like Hook Rate, Hold Rate, View Rate, and CVR to continuously define and refine what makes a winning asset based on current platform algorithms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop Growth Strategies:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Develop playbooks, content testing frameworks, new formats, and test strategies to unlock fresh growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Storytelling &amp;amp; Trust Building: &lt;/strong&gt;Master the art of communicating the brand story through performance creatives. Design narratives that authentically connect with customers, building the crucial trust needed to bridge the gap between initial engagement and final conversion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Connect Creative to Business Impact:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner closely with Business Analysts to bridge the gap between top-of-funnel ad metrics and bottom-line business results. Ensure every creative testing plan is grounded in driving tangible business outcomes (e.g., lower CAC, higher LTV, higher AOV, revenue growth) rather than purely focusing on brand awareness or aesthetics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initiate Creative Testing Plans: &lt;/strong&gt;Build and drive rigorous, structured testing frameworks

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Head of BI Analytics will be responsible for leading CASETiFY’s business intelligence and analytics capability, with a strong focus on data visualization, KPI setup, metadata establishment, and insight analysis across the organization. The incumbent will work closely with business, product, engineering, operations, finance, and leadership teams to ensure data is translated into clear, trusted, and actionable insights that support decision-making and performance management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The incumbent is expected to bring strong hands-on experience in BI analytics, dashboarding, KPI framework design, metadata and metric governance, and insight generation. This role will help establish a scalable and trusted analytics foundation, improve reporting consistency, and drive stronger business understanding in a fast-paced and dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and lead the BI analytics strategy, roadmap, priorities, and operating model in alignment with CASETiFY’s business goals and data maturity objectives,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and enhance business intelligence capabilities across the organization with strong focus on data visualization, management reporting, KPI setup, metadata standards, and insight analysis,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with business stakeholders to define, standardize, and govern KPIs, metric logic, business definitions, and reporting requirements across commercial, customer, supply chain, finance, and operational domains,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain a strong metadata foundation including metric definitions, business glossaries, reporting logic, semantic consistency, ownership, and documentation standards,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design, development, and continuous improvement of dashboards, scorecards, executive reports, and self-service reporting solutions that provide timely and actionable insights,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data visualization and reporting outputs are clear, intuitive, accurate, and aligned with business priorities and decision-making needs,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business questions and operational challenges into analytical frameworks, insight narratives, and practical recommendations that support performance improvement,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Data Engineering and platform teams to ensure underlying data structures, datasets, and semantic layers support high-quality and scalable BI analytics delivery,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive reporting consistency and single source of truth practices by aligning metric definitions, metadata, and dashboard logic across teams and functions,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support executive and management reporting needs through structured insight analysis, trend interpretation, variance analysis, and business performance review materials,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, mentor, and lead a high-performing BI analytics team, fostering strong business understanding, analytical rigor, visualization quality, and continuous improvement,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to CASETiFY’s data-driven culture by improving the quality, consistency, and business relevance of analytics across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on experience in BI analytics, dashboarding, data visualization, KPI framework design, and management reporting,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in building and leading BI analytics capabilities that support decision-making, performance management, and business insight generation,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in defining and governing KPIs, metric hierarchies, business definitions, metadata standards, and reporting logic across multiple business functions,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CASETiFY is one of the leading global lifestyle brands to offer customizable tech accessories. We’re industry leaders when it comes to trend forecasting and protecting what matters most; the community platform for creativity and self-expression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an international company that cares about culture and diversity. Our group is headquartered in Hong Kong and has offices in Los Angeles, Seoul, Shanghai, Taipei, Tokyo and our team comes from 27+ nationalities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We stand up for what we believe in by supporting causes that matter to us and our global community. At CASETiFY, we embrace diversity and inclusivity. As an equal opportunity employer, we encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply. We are also committed to sponsoring work visas on behalf of qualified candidates if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CASETiFY is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Influencer Marketing Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to scale our TikTok paid influencer marketing efforts across key global markets. This role will be responsible for end-to-end management of paid creator campaigns on TikTok - from influencer identification, negotiation, and booking through to content delivery, Spark Ads activation, and performance analysis. The position reports to the Marketing department and will work closely with the Growth Marketing, Integrated Marketing, and Influencer teams to drive measurable ROI through TikTok creator partnerships that strengthen CASETiFY&#39;s brand presence and accelerate business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute CASETiFY&#39;s TikTok paid influencer marketing strategy, identifying high-performing creators across target markets that align with brand and commercial objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end campaign lifecycle for TikTok paid partnerships — from creator sourcing, outreach, and negotiation through to briefing, content review, posting coordination, and Spark Ads/allowlisting activation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact between CASETiFY and agency partners, leading regular check-ins, reviewing deliverables, providing feedback, and escalating issues when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow an in-house roster of TikTok creators across multiple tiers (nano, micro, mid, macro), focusing on performance-driven content that converts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate competitive rates and contract terms with creators, talent agencies, and external partners, manage campaign budgets, and ensure cost efficiency at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and analyze campaign performance across key metrics, including CPM, CPV, CPA, ROAS, engagement rate, and conversion — delivering regular reporting with actionable insights and optimization recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain scalable processes, documentation, and tools (e.g., creator databases, campaign trackers, performance dashboards) to support the growth of the TikTok influencer program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on TikTok platform updates, algorithm shifts, trending formats, creator economy trends, and competitor activity to inform strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Requirement&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in social media, influencer management, digital or growth marketing, or related areas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in Marketing, Communications, Media Studies, or a related field preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong familiarity with TikTok, Instagram, YouTube Shorts, and other short-form content platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with strong attention to detail and accountability in managing workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in social media/performance marketing

